{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897502528,"sessionID":"ses_28442d047ffenRZ1MpYw8Va1pB","part":{"id":"prt_d7bbd603b001N0CgD8ZgLehOZB","messageID":"msg_d7bbd404c001eb4AZmnyuGVIK5","sessionID":"ses_28442d047ffenRZ1MpYw8Va1pB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d1f977f55fa34a5fb49d0c7c8e960b18","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for the Helm Chart templates and Values configuration for deploying the AgentCube platform components. It extends the base deployment specifications with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios for all chart operations, configuration options, and lifecycle management.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Chart.yaml metadata validation\n10: \n11: The system SHALL provide a valid Helm Chart.yaml with proper metadata and version information.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Chart.yaml contains required metadata fields\n14: - **GIVEN** a Helm chart directory structure exists\n15: - **WHEN** the Chart.yaml file is present\n16: - **THEN** it SHALL contain fields: apiVersion, name, description, type, version, appVersion\n17: - **AND** apiVersion SHALL be set to v2\n18: - **AND** type SHALL be set to application\n19: - **AND** version SHALL follow semantic versioning (e.g., 1.0.0)\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Chart keywords and maintainers are present\n22: - **GIVEN** a valid Chart.yaml file\n23: - **WHEN** inspecting the chart metadata\n24: - **THEN** keywords SHALL include relevant terms: agentcube, ai, code-interpreter, agent-runtime\n25: - **AND** maintainers SHALL be defined with name and email fields\n26: \n27: ### Requirement: Default values.yaml structure\n28: \n29: The system SHALL provide a comprehensive default values.yaml with all configurable parameters.\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Global configuration section exists\n32: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n33: - **WHEN** reading the global configuration section\n34: - **THEN** it SHALL include: imageRegistry, imagePullSecrets, namespace, labels\n35: - **AND** imageRegistry SHALL default to empty string (allow Docker Hub)\n36: - **AND** imagePullSecrets SHALL default to empty list\n37: - **AND** namespace SHALL default to agentcube\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: Controller Manager configuration exists\n40: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n41: - **WHEN** reading the controllerManager section\n42: - **THEN** it SHALL include: enabled, replicaCount, image, service, resources, nodeSelector, tolerations, affinity\n43: - **AND** enabled SHALL default to true\n44: - **AND** replicaCount SHALL default to 2\n45: - **AND** image.repository SHALL default to agentcube/controller-manager\n46: - **AND** image.pullPolicy SHALL default to IfNotPresent\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Workload Manager configuration exists\n49: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n50: - **WHEN** reading the workloadManager section\n51: - **THEN** it SHALL include: enabled, replicaCount, image, service, resources, nodeSelector, tolerations, affinity\n52: - **AND** enabled SHALL default to true\n53: - **AND** replicaCount SHALL default to 2\n54: - **AND** image.repository SHALL default to agentcube/workload-manager\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Router configuration exists\n57: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n58: - **WHEN** reading the router section\n59: - **THEN** it SHALL include: enabled, replicaCount, image, service, resources, nodeSelector, tolerations, affinity\n60: - **AND** enabled SHALL default to true\n61: - **AND** replicaCount SHALL default to 3\n62: - **AND** image.repository SHALL default to agentcube/router\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: RBAC configuration exists\n65: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n66: - **WHEN** reading the rbac section\n67: - **THEN** it SHALL include: create field\n68: - **AND** create SHALL default to true\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Monitoring configuration exists\n71: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n72: - **WHEN** reading the monitoring section\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL include: enabled and serviceMonitor fields\n74: - **AND** enabled SHALL default to false\n75: - **AND** serviceMonitor.enabled SHALL default to false\n76: - **AND** serviceMonitor.interval SHALL default to 30s\n77: - **AND** serviceMonitor.scrapeTimeout SHALL default to 10s\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: Security contexts are configured\n80: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n81: - **WHEN** reading the security context sections\n82: - **THEN** podSecurityContext SHALL include: runAsNonRoot, runAsUser, fsGroup\n83: - **AND** runAsNonRoot SHALL default to true\n84: - **AND** runAsUser SHALL default to 1000\n85: - **AND** containerSecurityContext SHALL include: allowPrivilegeEscalation, capabilities, readOnlyRootFilesystem\n86: - **AND** allowPrivilegeEscalation SHALL default to false\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: CRD template installation\n89: \n90: The system SHALL install Custom Resource Definitions as part of the Helm chart.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: CRD templates exist in correct location\n93: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart templates directory\n94: - **WHEN** listing the templates/crds/ directory\n95: - **THEN** agentruntime.yaml SHALL be present\n96: - **AND** codeinterpreter.yaml SHALL be present\n97: - **AND** CRD templates SHALL use helm.sh/resource-policy: keep annotation\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: CRDs install with correct metadata\n100: - **GIVEN** a Helm install command is executed\n101: - **WHEN** the CRD templates are rendered and applied\n102: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n103: - **AND** version SHALL be v1alpha1\n104: - **AND** scope SHALL be Namespaced\n105: - **AND** CRDs SHALL be installed before other resources\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: CRDs support version upgrades\n108: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentCube CRD installation\n109: - **WHEN** upgrading to a new chart version with CRD changes\n110: - **THEN** the CRDs SHALL be updated using helm.sh/hook: crd-install\n111: - **AND** existing CRD instances SHALL be preserved during upgrade\n112: - **AND** the upgrade SHALL not break existing resources\n113: \n114: ### Requirement: Controller Manager deployment template\n115: \n116: The system SHALL provide a Deployment template for the Controller Manager component.\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Controller Manager Deployment renders correctly\n119: - **GIVEN** the controller-manager/deployment.yaml template\n120: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with default values\n121: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL be named agentcube-controller-manager\n122: - **AND** replicas SHALL match controllerManager.replicaCount from values\n123: - **AND** the container SHALL use the image specified in values\n124: - **AND** imagePullPolicy SHALL match the configured value\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: Controller Manager Service is created\n127: - **GIVEN** the controller-manager/service.yaml template\n128: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n129: - **THEN** the Service SHALL be named agentcube-controller-manager\n130: - **AND** the Service type SHALL match controllerManager.service.type\n131: - **AND** the Service port SHALL match controllerManager.service.port\n132: - **AND** the Service SHALL target port 8080\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: Controller Manager ServiceAccount is created\n135: - **GIVEN** the controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml template\n136: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with rbac.create=true\n137: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount SHALL be created for the Controller Manager\n138: - **AND** the ServiceAccount SHALL have appropriate labels\n139: - **AND** the Deployment SHALL use this ServiceAccount\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Controller Manager disabled via values\n142: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with controllerManager.enabled=false\n143: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n144: - **THEN** Controller Manager Deployment SHALL NOT be created\n145: - **AND** Controller Manager Service SHALL NOT be created\n146: - **AND** Controller Manager ServiceAccount SHALL NOT be created\n147: \n148: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment template\n149: \n150: The system SHALL provide a Deployment template for the Workload Manager component.\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Workload Manager Deployment renders correctly\n153: - **GIVEN** the workload-manager/deployment.yaml template\n154: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with default values\n155: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL be named workloadmanager\n156: - **AND** replicas SHALL match workloadManager.replicaCount from values\n157: - **AND** the container SHALL expose HTTP on port 8080\n158: - **AND** liveness and readiness probes SHALL be configured\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: Workload Manager health checks are configured\n161: - **GIVEN** the Workload Manager Deployment template\n162: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n163: - **THEN** livenessProbe SHALL be configured with HTTP GET /health\n164: - **AND** readinessProbe SHALL be configured with HTTP GET /health\n165: - **AND** both probes SHALL use port 8080\n166: - **AND** initialDelaySeconds SHALL be 10\n167: - **AND** periodSeconds SHALL be 10\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Workload Manager Service is created\n170: - **GIVEN** the workload-manager/service.yaml template\n171: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n172: - **THEN** the Service SHALL be named workloadmanager\n173: - **AND** the Service type SHALL be ClusterIP\n174: - **AND** the Service SHALL expose port matching values configuration\n175: - **AND** the Service SHALL select pods with correct labels\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Workload Manager disabled via values\n178: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with workloadManager.enabled=false\n179: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n180: - **THEN** Workload Manager Deployment SHALL NOT be created\n181: - **AND** Workload Manager Service SHALL NOT be created\n182: - **AND** Workload Manager ServiceAccount SHALL NOT be created\n183: \n184: ### Requirement: Router deployment template\n185: \n186: The system SHALL provide a Deployment template for the Router component.\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: Router Deployment renders correctly\n189: - **GIVEN** the router/deployment.yaml template\n190: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with default values\n191: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL be named agentcube-router\n192: - **AND** replicas SHALL match router.replicaCount from values\n193: - **AND** the container SHALL expose HTTP on port 8080\n194: - **AND** container args SHALL include --port=<targetPort> and --debug\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Router configures Workload Manager URL\n197: - **GIVEN** the Router Deployment template\n198: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered in namespace N\n199: - **THEN** the Router pod SHALL have WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable\n200: - **AND** WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL SHALL be set to http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P\n201: - **AND** P SHALL be the Workload Manager service port from values\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: Router Service supports multiple types\n204: - **GIVEN** the router/service.yaml template\n205: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with router.service.type=LoadBalancer\n206: - **THEN** the Service SHALL be of type LoadBalancer\n207: - **AND** the Service SHALL be named agentcube-router\n208: - **AND** externalTrafficPolicy SHALL be set to Local (if applicable)\n209: - **AND** annotations SHALL be preserved from values\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Router disabled via values\n212: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with router.enabled=false\n213: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n214: - **THEN** Router Deployment SHALL NOT be created\n215: - **AND** Router Service SHALL NOT be created\n216: - **AND** Router ServiceAccount SHALL NOT be created\n217: \n218: ### Requirement: RBAC resources creation\n219: \n220: The system SHALL create appropriate RBAC resources for all components when enabled.\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole is created\n223: - **GIVEN** rbac.create=true in values\n224: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n225: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named workloadmanager SHALL be created\n226: - **AND** a ClusterRole named workloadmanager SHALL be created\n227: - **AND** a ClusterRoleBinding named workloadmanager SHALL be created\n228: - **AND** the Binding SHALL tie the ServiceAccount to the ClusterRole\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole has required permissions\n231: - **GIVEN** the Workload Manager ClusterRole template\n232: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n233: - **THEN** rules SHALL include permissions for agent-sandbox resources\n234: - **AND** rules SHALL include permissions for AgentCube runtime CRDs\n235: - **AND** rules SHALL include permissions for core workloads (pods, deployments)\n236: - **AND** rules SHALL include permissions for auth (tokenreviews)\n237: - **AND** rules SHALL include permissions for secrets\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Router RBAC is optional\n240: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with router.rbac.create=true\n241: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n242: - **THEN** Router ServiceAccount SHALL be created\n243: - **AND** Router Role SHALL be created in the release namespace\n244: - **AND** Router RoleBinding SHALL be created\n245: - **AND** the Role SHALL allow verbs on secrets in that namespace\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: RBAC disabled via values\n248: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with rbac.create=false\n249: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n250: - **THEN** no RBAC resources SHALL be created\n251: - **AND** Deployments SHALL use default ServiceAccount\n252: \n253: ### Requirement: Resource limits and requests\n254: \n255: The system SHALL support configurable resource limits and requests for all components.\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: Default resources are applied\n258: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml with resource specifications\n259: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n260: - **THEN** each component Deployment SHALL have resource requests\n261: - **AND** requests.cpu SHALL be 100m by default\n262: - **AND** requests.memory SHALL be 128Mi by default\n263: - **AND** limits.cpu SHALL be 500m by default\n264: - **AND** limits.memory SHALL be 512Mi by default\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: Custom resources override defaults\n267: - **GIVEN** custom values.yaml with custom resource specifications\n268: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with custom values\n269: - **THEN** resource requests SHALL match the custom values\n270: - **AND** resource limits SHALL match the custom values\n271: - **AND** default values SHALL be overridden\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Resources can be disabled\n274: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with empty resource sections\n275: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n276: - **THEN** containers SHALL NOT have resource requests\n277: - **AND** containers SHALL NOT have resource limits\n278: \n279: ### Requirement: Node selectors and affinity\n280: \n281: The system SHALL support node selectors and affinity rules for pod scheduling.\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: Node selectors are applied\n284: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with nodeSelector configuration\n285: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n286: - **THEN** each component Deployment SHALL have the specified nodeSelector\n287: - **AND** pods SHALL only schedule on matching nodes\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: Tolerations are applied\n290: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with tolerations configuration\n291: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n292: - **THEN** each component Deployment SHALL have the specified tolerations\n293: - **AND** pods SHALL be able to schedule on tainted nodes\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: Affinity rules are applied\n296: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with affinity configuration\n297: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n298: - **THEN** each component Deployment SHALL have the specified affinity rules\n299: - **AND** podAntiAffinity rules SHALL be respected during scheduling\n300: \n301: ### Requirement: High availability configuration\n302: \n303: The system SHALL support high availability through replica count and anti-affinity configuration.\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: Multiple replicas are scheduled\n306: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with controllerManager.replicaCount=3\n307: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n308: - **THEN** the Controller Manager Deployment SHALL have 3 replicas\n309: - **AND** 3 pods SHALL be scheduled (subject to resource availability)\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Pod anti-affinity prevents single node failure\n312: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with podAntiAffinity configuration\n313: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n314: - **THEN** pods SHALL have anti-affinity rules configured\n315: - **AND** pods SHALL prefer to run on different nodes\n316: - **AND** pod disruption budget SHALL prevent single node failures\n317: \n318: ### Requirement: Monitoring integration\n319: \n320: The system SHALL support optional Prometheus monitoring through ServiceMonitor resources.\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: ServiceMonitor is not created by default\n323: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with monitoring.enabled=false (default)\n324: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n325: - **THEN** no ServiceMonitor resources SHALL be created\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: ServiceMonitor is created when enabled\n328: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with monitoring.enabled=true and serviceMonitor.enabled=true\n329: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n330: - **THEN** ServiceMonitor resources SHALL be created for each enabled component\n331: - **AND** ServiceMonitor interval SHALL match values configuration\n332: - **AND** ServiceMonitor scrapeTimeout SHALL match values configuration\n333: - **AND** ServiceMonitor SHALL select pods with appropriate labels\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: ServiceMonitor labels are configurable\n336: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with custom serviceMonitor labels\n337: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n338: - **THEN** ServiceMonitor SHALL have the specified labels\n339: - **AND** Prometheus SHALL discover the ServiceMonitor based on labels\n340: \n341: ### Requirement: Image pull secrets and registry configuration\n342: \n343: The system SHALL support configuring image registry and pull secrets.\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Global image registry is applied\n346: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with global.imageRegistry=registry.example.com\n347: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n348: - **THEN** all component images SHALL use the registry.example.com prefix\n349: - **AND** image references SHALL be formatted as registry.example.com/component:tag\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: Image pull secrets are configured\n352: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with global.imagePullSecrets=[my-secret]\n353: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n354: - **THEN** all component ServiceAccounts SHALL have imagePullSecrets\n355: - **AND** the secret my-secret SHALL be referenced\n356: - **AND** multiple secrets SHALL be supported\n357: \n358: #### Scenario: Component-specific image tags override global\n359: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with global image configuration and component-specific tags\n360: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n361: - **THEN** component-specific image tags SHALL take precedence over global settings\n362: - **AND** each component SHALL use its configured tag\n363: \n364: ### Requirement: Development environment configuration\n365: \n366: The system SHALL provide a values-dev.yaml file for development deployments.\n367: \n368: #### Scenario: Dev values use minimal resources\n369: - **GIVEN** the values-dev.yaml file\n370: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-dev.yaml\n371: - **THEN** component replicaCounts SHALL be 1\n372: - **AND** resource requests SHALL be minimal (e.g., 50m cpu, 64Mi memory)\n373: - **AND** resource limits SHALL be conservative\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: Dev values disable monitoring\n376: - **GIVEN** the values-dev.yaml file\n377: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-dev.yaml\n378: - **THEN** monitoring SHALL be disabled\n379: - **AND** no ServiceMonitor resources SHALL be created\n380: \n381: #### Scenario: Dev values allow insecure configurations\n382: - **GIVEN** the values-dev.yaml file\n383: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-dev.yaml\n384: - **THEN** security contexts MAY be relaxed for development\n385: - **AND** debug flags MAY be enabled\n386: \n387: ### Requirement: Production environment configuration\n388: \n389: The system SHALL provide a values-prod.yaml file for production deployments.\n390: \n391: #### Scenario: Prod values use high availability configuration\n392: - **GIVEN** the values-prod.yaml file\n393: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-prod.yaml\n394: - **THEN** Controller Manager replicaCount SHALL be 2 or more\n395: - **AND** Workload Manager replicaCount SHALL be 2 or more\n396: - **AND** Router replicaCount SHALL be 3 or more\n397: \n398: #### Scenario: Prod values enable monitoring\n399: - **GIVEN** the values-prod.yaml file\n400: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-prod.yaml\n401: - **THEN** monitoring SHALL be enabled\n402: - **AND** ServiceMonitor SHALL be created\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: Prod values configure pod anti-affinity\n405: - **GIVEN** the values-prod.yaml file\n406: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-prod.yaml\n407: - **THEN** podAntiAffinity rules SHALL be configured\n408: - **AND** pods SHALL prefer different nodes\n409: - **AND** PodDisruptionBudget SHALL be configured\n410: \n411: #### Scenario: Prod values use production resources\n412: - **GIVEN** the values-prod.yaml file\n413: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered with -f values-prod.yaml\n414: - **THEN** resource requests SHALL be appropriate for production load\n415: - **AND** resource limits SHALL be configured to prevent resource exhaustion\n416: \n417: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation workflow\n418: \n419: The system SHALL support standard Helm installation, upgrade, and rollback workflows.\n420: \n421: #### Scenario: Fresh install with default values\n422: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3\n423: - **WHEN** running `helm install agentcube ./agentcube --namespace agentcube --create-namespace`\n424: - **THEN** all CRDs SHALL be installed\n425: - **AND** all enabled components SHALL be deployed\n426: - **AND** all Services SHALL be created\n427: - **AND** all RBAC resources SHALL be created\n428: - **AND** pods SHALL become ready within reasonable time\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: Install with custom values file\n431: - **GIVEN** a custom values file custom-values.yaml\n432: - **WHEN** running `helm install agentcube ./agentcube -f custom-values.yaml`\n433: - **THEN** the installation SHALL use the custom values\n434: - **AND** all customizations SHALL be applied\n435: - **AND** default values SHALL be overridden where specified\n436: \n437: #### Scenario: Install with inline values\n438: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart\n439: - **WHEN** running `helm install agentcube ./agentcube --set controllerManager.replicaCount=5`\n440: - **THEN** the Controller Manager SHALL use 5 replicas\n441: - **AND** other components SHALL use default values\n442: \n443: #### Scenario: Upgrade preserves existing configuration\n444: - **GIVEN** an existing Helm installation\n445: - **WHEN** running `helm upgrade agentcube ./agentcube`\n446: - **THEN** existing resources SHALL be updated in-place\n447: - **AND** persistent data SHALL be preserved\n448: - **AND** pods SHALL be restarted gracefully\n449: \n450: #### Scenario: Rollback restores previous version\n451: - **GIVEN** a Helm installation that has been upgraded\n452: - **WHEN** running `helm rollback agentcube`\n453: - **THEN** the chart SHALL be restored to the previous version\n454: - **AND** all resources SHALL be reverted to previous state\n455: - **AND** the rollback SHALL not cause downtime\n456: \n457: #### Scenario: Uninstall removes all resources\n458: - **GIVEN** an existing Helm installation\n459: - **WHEN** running `helm uninstall agentcube`\n460: - **THEN** all Deployments SHALL be deleted\n461: - **AND** all Services SHALL be deleted\n462: - **AND** all RBAC resources SHALL be deleted\n463: - **AND** CRDs SHALL be kept (due to resource-policy: keep annotation)\n464: \n465: ### Requirement: Chart documentation\n466: \n467: The system SHALL provide comprehensive documentation for the Helm chart.\n468: \n469: #### Scenario: README.md contains installation instructions\n470: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart README.md file\n471: - **WHEN** reading the documentation\n472: - **THEN** it SHALL contain installation instructions\n473: - **AND** it SHALL describe all configuration options\n474: - **AND** it SHALL provide example values files\n475: - **AND** it SHALL include troubleshooting guidance\n476: \n477: #### Scenario: values.yaml has inline comments\n478: - **GIVEN** the default values.yaml file\n479: - **WHEN** inspecting the values\n480: - **THEN** each configuration section SHALL have descriptive comments\n481: - **AND** important parameters SHALL be documented\n482: - **AND** default values SHALL be explained\n483: \n484: #### Scenario: NOTES.txt provides post-install information\n485: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart templates/NOTES.txt file\n486: - **WHEN** an installation completes\n487: - **THEN** useful information SHALL be displayed\n488: - **AND** the information SHALL include: how to access services, how to check status, next steps\n489: \n490: ### Requirement: Template validation and linting\n491: \n492: The system SHALL provide valid templates that pass Helm linting.\n493: \n494: #### Scenario: Chart passes helm lint\n495: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart directory\n496: - **WHEN** running `helm lint ./agentcube`\n497: - **THEN** the linting SHALL pass without errors\n498: - **AND** no warnings SHALL be raised\n499: \n500: #### Scenario: Chart passes helm template render\n501: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart directory\n502: - **WHEN** running `helm template test ./agentcube`\n503: - **THEN** the template SHALL render successfully\n504: - **AND** valid YAML SHALL be produced\n505: - **AND** no rendering errors SHALL occur\n506: \n507: #### Scenario: Chart syntax is valid\n508: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart templates\n509: - **WHEN** validating Go template syntax\n510: - **THEN** all templates SHALL have valid syntax\n511: - **AND** all variables SHALL be properly referenced\n512: - **AND** all conditionals SHALL be properly formatted\n513: \n514: ---\n515: \n516: ## Backward Compatibility\n517: \n518: This delta specification introduces new Helm Chart functionality without breaking changes to existing deployment methods. The Helm chart is an additional deployment option that can coexist with existing manual YAML deployment approaches.\n519: \n520: ## Dependencies\n521: \n522: This delta specification depends on:\n523: - Kubernetes 1.20+ (as specified in base requirements)\n524: - Helm 3.0+ for chart installation and management\n525: - Base deployment specifications: `deployment/spec.md`\n526: - Existing CRD definitions: `config/crd/bases/`\n527: - Base component configurations from `deployment/spec.md`\n528: \n529: ## Breaking Changes\n530: \n531: None. This delta specification defines a new Helm Chart deployment mechanism that provides an alternative to existing deployment methods without introducing breaking changes to existing functionality or APIs.\n532: \n533: ## Security Considerations\n534: \n535: 1. **RBAC Permissions**: The chart creates RBAC resources with minimal required permissions following the principle of least privilege\n536: 2. **Secrets Management**: The chart supports pulling images from private registries using image pull secrets without storing secrets in values files\n537: 3. **Security Contexts**: The chart applies non-root user, read-only filesystem, and dropped capabilities by default\n538: 4. **Network Policies**: While not explicitly required in this spec, the chart should support network policy configuration for pod-to-pod communication\n539: 5. **Image Security**: The chart supports image pull policy configuration and private registry authentication\n540: \n541: ## Testing Strategy\n542: \n543: ### Template Tests\n544: - Verify all templates render correctly with default values\n545: - Verify all templates render correctly with custom values\n546: - Verify templates fail gracefully with invalid values\n547: - Verify CRD templates install and upgrade correctly\n548: \n549: ### Installation Tests\n550: - Test fresh installation with default values\n551: - Test installation with custom values files\n552: - Test installation with inline value overrides\n553: - Verify all resources are created correctly\n554: - Verify pods become ready and services are accessible\n555: \n556: ### Upgrade Tests\n557: - Test upgrade from one chart version to another\n558: - Verify existing resources are updated in-place\n559: - Verify data persistence during upgrades\n560: - Verify no downtime during upgrades\n561: \n562: ### Rollback Tests\n563: - Test rollback to previous chart version\n564: - Verify resources are restored to previous state\n565: - Verify no data loss during rollback\n566: \n567: ### Multi-Environment Tests\n568: - Test deployment with values-dev.yaml\n569: - Test deployment with values-prod.yaml\n570: - Verify environment-specific configurations are applied\n571: \n572: ### Integration Tests\n573: - Test interaction between components (Router → Workload Manager)\n574: - Verify service discovery works correctly\n575: - Test RBAC permissions are correct\n576: - Verify CRDs can be created and managed\n577: \n578: ### Validation Tests\n579: - Run `helm lint` to verify chart syntax\n580: - Run `helm template` to verify rendering\n581: - Verify Chart.yaml follows Helm best practices\n582: - Verify values.yaml is properly structured and documented\n\n(End of file - total 582 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for the Helm Chart templates and Values configuration for deploying the AgentCube platform components. It extends the base deployment specifications with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios for all chart operations, configuration options, and lifecycle management.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Chart.yaml metadata validation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a valid Helm Chart.yaml with proper metadata and version information.\n\n#### Scenario: Chart.yaml contains required metadata fields\n- **GIVEN** a Helm chart directory structure exists\n- **WHEN** the Chart.yaml file is present\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain fields: apiVersion, name, description, type, version, appVersion\n- **AND** apiVersion SHALL be set to v2\n- **AND** type SHALL be set to application\n- **AND** version SHALL follow semantic versioning (e.g., 1.0.0)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775897502497,"end":1775897502525}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897502531,"sessionID":"ses_28442d047ffenRZ1MpYw8Va1pB","part":{"id":"prt_d7bbd63030017Te1Q81lM3Oopf","messageID":"msg_d7bbd404c001eb4AZmnyuGVIK5","sessionID":"ses_28442d047ffenRZ1MpYw8Va1pB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-92cb64d6e21b4e688e3393698bc9ba24","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015 Delta Specification: PicoD 命令执行 API\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 实现 PicoD HTTP 守护进程的命令执行 API，为 AgentCube 平台的代码解释器沙箱提供安全的代码执行和文件管理能力。PicoD 在可配置的工作区 jail 中运行命令，管理工作区文件，并暴露健康检查端点和 JWT（RSA）保护的 API。\n6: \n7: ## Base Specs\n8: \n9: - code-execution/spec.md: PicoD 命令执行 API 规范，包含所有 API 端点和行为的详细定义\n10: - code-execution/design.md: PicoD 设计文档，从源码推导的数据结构、常量和实现细节\n11: - deployment/client-go.md: Kubernetes 客户端库，用于 runtime API 类型（AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter CRDs）\n12: - proposal.md: AR-015 提案文档，概述 PicoD 的目的、范围、设计和实现策略\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: HTTP 服务器初始化\n17: \n18: 系统 SHALL 初始化 Gin HTTP 服务器，使用可配置的监听端口和工作区根目录。\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: 使用默认配置初始化服务器\n21: - **GIVEN** 未提供 `-port` 和 `-workspace` 标志\n22: - **WHEN** PicoD 服务器启动\n23: - **THEN** 端口默认为 8080\n24: - **AND** 工作区根目录默认为当前工作目录\n25: - **AND** Gin 运行在 ReleaseMode\n26: - **AND** 全局中间件包括 Logger 和 Recovery\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: 使用自定义端口初始化服务器\n29: - **GIVEN** 提供 `-port 9090` 标志\n30: - **WHEN** PicoD 服务器启动\n31: - **THEN** 服务器监听在端口 9090\n32: - **AND** 配置使用指定的端口\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: 使用自定义工作区初始化服务器\n35: - **GIVEN** 提供 `-workspace /data/workspace` 标志\n36: - **WHEN** PicoD 服务器启动\n37: - **THEN** 工作区根目录设置为 `/data/workspace`\n38: - **AND** 目录路径被解析为绝对路径\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: 服务器配置 ReadHeaderTimeout\n41: - **GIVEN** PicoD 服务器启动\n42: - **WHEN** HTTP 服务器配置完成\n43: - **THEN** ReadHeaderTimeout 设置为 10 秒\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: JWT 认证管理器\n46: \n47: 系统 SHALL 使用 RSA 公钥实现 JWT 认证管理器，用于验证 API 请求。\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: 从环境变量加载公钥\n50: - **GIVEN** 环境变量 `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` 设置为有效的 PEM 编码的 RSA 公钥\n51: - **WHEN** AuthManager 初始化\n52: - **THEN** 公钥成功加载并解析\n53: - **AND** 管理器准备好验证 JWT 令牌\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: 缺少公钥导致致命错误\n56: - **GIVEN** 环境变量 `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` 未设置\n57: - **WHEN** AuthManager 尝试加载公钥\n58: - **THEN** 记录致命错误\n59: - **AND** 进程退出而不继续服务\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: 无效的 PEM 格式导致致命错误\n62: - **GIVEN** 环境变量 `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` 包含无效的 PEM 数据\n63: - **WHEN** AuthManager 尝试解析 PEM 块\n64: - **THEN** 记录致命错误\n65: - **AND** 进程退出\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: 非 RSA 公钥导致致命错误\n68: - **GIVEN** 环境变量 `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` 包含有效的 PEM 公钥但不是 RSA 类型\n69: - **WHEN** AuthManager 尝试解析为 RSA 公钥\n70: - **THEN** 记录致命错误\n71: - **AND** 进程退出\n72: \n73: ### Requirement: JWT 认证中间件\n74: \n75: 系统 SHALL 为 `/api/*` 路由提供 JWT 认证中间件。\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: 缺少授权头\n78: - **GIVEN** 请求没有 `Authorization` 头\n79: - **WHEN** 请求到达 `/api/*` 端点\n80: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 401\n81: - **AND** JSON 包含 `\"error\"` 和 `\"code\"` 字段\n82: - **AND** JSON 包含 `\"detail\"` 字段说明缺失头\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: 无效的授权头格式\n85: - **GIVEN** 授权头不是两个空格分隔的部分或第一部分不是 `Bearer`\n86: - **WHEN** 请求到达 `/api/*` 端点\n87: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 401\n88: - **AND** 错误消息指示使用 `Bearer <token>` 格式\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: 无效的 JWT 签名\n91: - **GIVEN** JWT 令牌签名无效\n92: - **WHEN** 中间件验证令牌\n93: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 401\n94: - **AND** 错误消息为 `\"Invalid token\"`\n95: - **AND** detail 包含验证错误\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: 过期的 JWT 令牌\n98: - **GIVEN** JWT 令牌已过期（`exp` 在过去）\n99: - **WHEN** 中间件验证令牌\n100: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 401\n101: - **AND** 错误消息为 `\"Invalid token\"`\n102: - **AND** detail 包含过期信息\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: 非 RSA 签名方法\n105: - **GIVEN** JWT 令牌使用 HS256（HMAC）签名\n106: - **WHEN** 中间件验证令牌\n107: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 401\n108: - **AND** 错误指示意外的签名方法\n109: \n110: #### Scenario: 有效的 JWT 令牌\n111: - **GIVEN** 有效的 RSA 签名 JWT 令牌在 `Authorization` 头中\n112: - **WHEN** 请求到达 `/api/*` 端点\n113: - **THEN** 请求传递到处理程序\n114: - **AND** 请求体被包装在 `http.MaxBytesReader` 中，限制为 32 MiB\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: JWT 验证选项\n117: - **GIVEN** JWT 令牌验证\n118: - **WHEN** 中间件验证令牌\n119: - **THEN** 使用 `WithExpirationRequired` 选项\n120: - **AND** 使用 `WithIssuedAt` 选项\n121: - **AND** 使用 `WithLeeway(1 minute)` 选项\n122: \n123: ### Requirement: 命令执行 API\n124: \n125: 系统 SHALL 接受 `POST /api/execute` 请求，执行命令并返回结果。\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: 有效执行使用默认超时\n128: - **GIVEN** 有效的 JWT 和 JSON body，包含非空 `command` 和空 `timeout`\n129: - **WHEN** 客户端调用 `POST /api/execute`\n130: - **THEN** 服务器使用 60 秒的默认超时\n131: - **AND** 运行命令\n132: - **AND** 返回包含 `stdout`、`stderr`、`exit_code`、`duration`、`start_time` 和 `end_time` 的 JSON\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: 有效执行使用自定义超时\n135: - **GIVEN** 有效的 JWT 和 JSON body，`timeout` 是可被 Go `time.ParseDuration` 解析的非空字符串（例如 `\"30s\"`、`\"500ms\"`）\n136: - **WHEN** 客户端调用 `POST /api/execute`\n137: - **THEN** 服务器使用该持续时间作为命令上下文超时\n138: - **AND** 命令在指定的超时内执行\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: 超时超过\n141: - **GIVEN** 执行超过上下文截止时间\n142: - **WHEN** 上下文被取消\n143: - **THEN** 响应 `exit_code` 为 `124`（`TimeoutExitCode`）\n144: - **AND** stderr 包含命令超时的消息，超时长度以秒为单位（整数格式）\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: 无效的超时格式\n147: - **GIVEN** `timeout` 非空但不是有效的持续时间\n148: - **WHEN** 客户端调用 `POST /api/execute`\n149: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 400\n150: - **AND** JSON `error` 描述无效的超时格式\n151: - **AND** `code` 为 400\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: 空命令\n154: - **GIVEN** JSON 绑定成功但 `command` 长度为零\n155: - **WHEN** 客户端调用 `POST /api/execute`\n156: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 400\n157: - **AND** `error` 为 `\"command cannot be empty\"`\n158: - **AND** `code` 为 400\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: 工作目录在工作区内\n161: - **GIVEN** `working_dir` 非空\n162: - **WHEN** 服务器使用与文件 API 相同的路径安全规则解析它\n163: - **THEN** `cmd.Dir` 设置为清理后的绝对路径\n164: - **AND** 如果解析失败，服务器响应 HTTP 400，`error` 前缀为 `\"Invalid working directory: \"`\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: 环境变量增强\n167: - **GIVEN** `env` 非空\n168: - **WHEN** 命令运行\n169: - **THEN** `cmd.Env` 是当前进程环境加上每个 map 条目的额外 `key=value` 条目\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: 格式错误的 JSON\n172: - **GIVEN** body 不是 `ExecuteRequest` 的有效 JSON\n173: - **WHEN** 绑定失败\n174: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 400\n175: - **AND** `error` 来自绑定器\n176: - **AND** `code` 为 400\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: 命令执行成功\n179: - **GIVEN** 有效的 `ExecuteRequest` 和工作区中可用的命令\n180: - **WHEN** 命令执行成功\n181: - **THEN** `exit_code` 为 0\n182: - **AND** `stdout` 包含命令输出\n183: - **AND** `stderr` 为空或包含错误输出\n184: - **AND** `duration` 记录执行时间\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: 命令执行失败\n187: - **GIVEN** 有效的 `ExecuteRequest` 但命令返回非零退出码\n188: - **WHEN** 命令执行完成\n189: - **THEN** `exit_code` 反映实际退出码\n190: - **AND** 服务器仍然返回 HTTP 200\n191: - **AND** `stdout` 和 `stderr` 捕获输出\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: 不接受 stdin\n194: - **GIVEN** 任何 `ExecuteRequest`\n195: - **WHEN** 命令执行\n196: - **THEN** `cmd.Stdin` 未设置\n197: - **AND** 进程不从请求体接收标准输入\n198: \n199: ### Requirement: 文件上传 API\n200: \n201: 系统 SHALL 接受 `POST /api/files` 请求，支持 multipart form-data 和 JSON Base64 格式。\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: Multipart 上传\n204: - **GIVEN** `Content-Type` 前缀为 `multipart/form-data`，表单字段 `path` 已设置，表单文件 `file` 存在\n205: - **WHEN** 客户端发布到 `POST /api/files`\n206: - **THEN** 服务器创建具有模式 `0755` 的父目录\n207: - **AND** 将上传的流写入清理后的路径\n208: - **AND** 从表单字段 `mode` 应用模式，通过 `parseFileMode`（默认 `0644`，当为空/无效/超过最大值时）\n209: - **AND** 响应 HTTP 200，使用 `path` 作为相对于工作区根目录的 `FileInfo`\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Multipart 缺少路径或文件\n212: - **GIVEN** multipart 请求中 `path` 为空或 `file` 缺失/不可读\n213: - **WHEN** 处理程序运行\n214: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 400\n215: - **AND** 适当的 `error` 消息\n216: - **AND** `code` 为 400\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: JSON Base64 上传\n219: - **GIVEN** 非 multipart 请求，包含必需的 JSON `path` 和 `content`（Base64 标准编码）\n220: - **WHEN** 客户端发布到 `POST /api/files`\n221: - **THEN** 服务器解码内容\n222: - **AND** 创建目录\n223: - **AND** 使用 `parseFileMode` 在 `mode` 上写入文件\n224: - **AND** 响应 HTTP 200，`FileInfo`（相对 `path`）\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: 无效的 Base64\n227: - **GIVEN** JSON 上传，`content` 中有无效的 Base64\n228: - **WHEN** 解码失败\n229: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 400\n230: - **AND** `error` 描述无效的 base64\n231: - **AND** `code` 为 400\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: 文件模式解析\n234: - **GIVEN** `mode` 字段提供\n235: - **WHEN** 解析文件模式\n236: - **THEN** 有效的八进制模式被应用\n237: - **AND** 无效模式回退到默认值 `0644`\n238: - **AND** 超过 `0777` 的模式回退到 `0644`\n239: \n240: ### Requirement: 文件列表 API\n241: \n242: 系统 SHALL 接受 `GET /api/files?path=...`，列出目录内容。\n243: \n244: #### Scenario: 成功列出\n245: - **GIVEN** `path` 指向工作区内存在的目录\n246: - **WHEN** 客户端调用 `GET /api/files?path=<dir>`\n247: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 200\n248: - **AND** `files` 是 `FileEntry` 对象数组（`name`、`size`、`modified`、`mode`、`is_dir`）\n249: - **AND** 跳过 `entry.Info()` 失败的条目\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: 缺少查询参数\n252: - **GIVEN** `path` 查询参数缺失或为空\n253: - **WHEN** 客户端调用 `GET /api/files`\n254: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 400\n255: - **AND** `error` 为 `\"Missing 'path' query parameter\"`\n256: - **AND** `code` 为 400\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: 目录未找到\n259: - **GIVEN** 清理后的路径不存在\n260: - **WHEN** `os.ReadDir` 失败，显示不存在\n261: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 404\n262: - **AND** `error` 为 `\"Directory not found\"`\n263: - **AND** `code` 为 404\n264: \n265: ### Requirement: 文件下载 API\n266: \n267: 系统 SHALL 在 `GET /api/files/*path` 提供文件内容。\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: 成功下载\n270: - **GIVEN** 通配符路径解析为工作区内的常规文件\n271: - **WHEN** 客户端调用 `GET /api/files/<path>`\n272: - **THEN** 服务器设置 `Content-Description` 为 `File Transfer`\n273: - **AND** `Content-Transfer-Encoding` 为 `binary`\n274: - **AND** `Content-Disposition` 为 `attachment; filename=\"<basename>\"`\n275: - **AND** `Content-Type` 来自 `mime.TypeByExtension` 或 `application/octet-stream`\n276: - **AND** 返回文件体\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: 路径逃逸工作区\n279: - **GIVEN** 请求的路径未能通过 `sanitizePath`\n280: - **WHEN** 客户端调用下载端点\n281: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 400\n282: - **AND** `error` 描述访问被拒绝/工作区 jail\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: 不是文件\n285: - **GIVEN** 路径存在但是目录\n286: - **WHEN** 客户端下载\n287: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 400\n288: - **AND** `error` 为 `\"Path is a directory, not a file\"`\n289: - **AND** `code` 为 400\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: 文件缺失\n292: - **GIVEN** 路径不存在\n293: - **WHEN** stat 失败，显示不存在\n294: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 404\n295: - **AND** `error` 为 `\"File not found\"`\n296: - **AND** `code` 为 404\n297: \n298: ### Requirement: 健康检查端点\n299: \n300: 系统 SHALL 暴露 `GET /health` 而无需 JWT 中间件。\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: 未认证的健康检查\n303: - **GIVEN** 没有 `Authorization` 头\n304: - **WHEN** 客户端调用 `GET /health`\n305: - **THEN** 服务器响应 HTTP 200\n306: - **AND** JSON 包含 `status` 为 `\"ok\"`\n307: - **AND** JSON 包含 `service` 为 `\"PicoD\"`\n308: - **AND** JSON 包含 `version` 为 `\"0.0.1\"`\n309: - **AND** JSON 包含 `uptime` 作为 `time.Since(server start)` 的字符串\n310: \n311: ### Requirement: 路径安全\n312: \n313: 系统 SHALL 通过 `sanitizePath` 函数强制执行工作区 jail。\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: 有效相对路径\n316: - **GIVEN** 工作区为 `/workspace`，请求路径为 `subdir/file.txt`\n317: - **WHEN** 调用 `sanitizePath`\n318: - **THEN** 返回 `/workspace/subdir/file.txt`\n319: - **AND** 路径在 jail 内\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: 绝对路径转换为相对\n322: - **GIVEN** 工作区为 `/workspace`，请求路径为 `/subdir/file.txt`\n323: - **WHEN** 调用 `sanitizePath`\n324: - **THEN** 去除前导路径分隔符\n325: - **AND** 解析为 `/workspace/subdir/file.txt`\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: 路径使用 `..` 逃逸\n328: - **GIVEN** 工作区为 `/workspace`，请求路径为 `../../etc/passwd`\n329: - **WHEN** 调用 `sanitizePath`\n330: - **THEN** 返回错误\n331: - **AND** 错误指示访问被拒绝\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: 符号链接逃逸\n334: - **GIVEN** 工作区内有指向工作区外的符号链接\n335: - **WHEN** 调用 `sanitizePath` 解析符号链接\n336: - **THEN** 解析最终路径\n337: - **AND** 重新检查相对于工作区的解析路径\n338: - **AND** 如果逃逸则拒绝\n339: \n340: #### Scenario: 符号链接到有效路径\n341: - **GIVEN** 工作区内有指向工作区内其他位置的符号链接\n342: - **WHEN** 调用 `sanitizePath` 解析符号链接\n343: - **THEN** 解析最终路径\n344: - **AND** 验证路径在工作区内\n345: - **AND** 返回清理后的路径\n346: \n347: ### Requirement: 错误响应格式\n348: \n349: 系统 SHALL 为所有错误返回一致的 JSON 响应格式。\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: 通用错误（400/500）\n352: - **GIVEN** HTTP 错误（400 或 500）\n353: - **WHEN** 返回错误响应\n354: - **THEN** JSON 包含 `error` 字符串\n355: - **AND** JSON 包含 `code` 整数（HTTP 状态码）\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: 认证错误（401）\n358: - **GIVEN** JWT 验证失败\n359: - **WHEN** 返回错误响应\n360: - **THEN** JSON 包含 `error` 字符串\n361: - **AND** JSON 包含 `code` 整数（401）\n362: - **AND** JSON 包含 `detail` 字符串，包含验证错误详情\n363: \n364: #### Scenario: 路径安全错误（400）\n365: - **GIVEN** 路径逃逸工作区\n366: - **WHEN** 返回错误响应\n367: - **THEN** JSON 包含 `error` 指示访问被拒绝\n368: - **AND** JSON 包含 `code` 为 400\n369: \n370: ### Requirement: 常量定义\n371: \n372: 系统 SHALL 定义用于配置和行为的适当常量。\n373: \n374: #### Scenario: 超时退出码\n375: - **GIVEN** 命令执行超时\n376: - **WHEN** 设置退出码\n377: - **THEN** 退出码为 `124`（`TimeoutExitCode`）\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: 最大主体大小\n380: - **GIVEN** JWT 验证成功后\n381: - **WHEN** 包装请求体\n382: - **THEN** 限制为 `32 << 20`（32 MiB）（`MaxBodySize`）\n383: \n384: #### Scenario: 公钥环境变量\n385: - **GIVEN** 加载 RSA 公钥\n386: - **WHEN** 读取环境变量\n387: - **THEN** 变量名为 `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`（`PublicKeyEnvVar`）\n388: \n389: #### Scenario: 默认超时\n390: - **GIVEN** 命令执行请求中未指定超时\n391: - **WHEN** 执行命令\n392: - **THEN** 默认超时为 60 秒\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: 默认文件模式\n395: - **GIVEN** 文件上传未指定模式或模式无效\n396: - **WHEN** 设置文件权限\n397: - **THEN** 默认模式为 `0644`（八进制）\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: 最大文件模式\n400: - **GIVEN** 文件上传指定模式\n401: - **WHEN** 解析文件模式\n402: - **THEN** 模式被限制为最大 `0777`（八进制）\n403: \n404: ### Requirement: CLI 标志集成\n405: \n406: 系统 SHALL 使用标准 Go flag 包支持 CLI 标志。\n407: \n408: #### Scenario: 端口标志\n409: - **GIVEN** 使用 `-port 9090` 启动 PicoD\n410: - **WHEN** 标志被解析\n411: - **THEN** 服务器配置使用端口 9090\n412: \n413: #### Scenario: 工作区标志\n414: - **GIVEN** 使用 `-workspace /data/workspace` 启动 PicoD\n415: - **WHEN** 标志被解析\n416: - **THEN** 服务器配置使用 `/data/workspace` 作为工作区根目录\n417: \n418: #### Scenario: klog 标志\n419: - **GIVEN** 使用任何 klog 标志启动 PicoD\n420: - **WHEN** 标志被解析\n421: - **THEN** klog 标志被注册并可用\n422: \n423: ### Requirement: Gin 路由注册\n424: \n425: 系统 SHALL 使用 Gin 框架正确注册路由。\n426: \n427: #### Scenario: API 路由分组\n428: - **GIVEN** Gin 引擎已创建\n429: - **WHEN** 注册路由\n430: - **THEN** `/api` 路由在组下注册\n431: - **AND** 组使用 `AuthMiddleware`\n432: - **AND** `/api/execute` 为 POST\n433: - **AND** `/api/files` 为 POST\n434: - **AND** `/api/files` 为 GET\n435: - **AND** `/api/files/*path` 为 GET\n436: \n437: #### Scenario: 健康检查路由\n438: - **GIVEN** Gin 引擎已创建\n439: - **WHEN** 注册路由\n440: - **THEN** `/health` 路由在全局级别注册\n441: - **AND** 不需要认证\n442: \n443: #### Scenario: 下载路径参数\n444: - **GIVEN** 请求到 `GET /api/files/subdir/file.txt`\n445: - **WHEN** 处理程序处理请求\n446: - **THEN** `c.Param(\"path\")` 返回 `/subdir/file.txt`\n447: - **AND** 前导 `/` 被去除\n448: \n449: ### Requirement: 服务器启动和运行\n450: \n451: 系统 SHALL 正确启动和运行 HTTP 服务器。\n452: \n453: #### Scenario: 成功启动\n454: - **GIVEN** 有效配置和 RSA 公钥\n455: - **WHEN** 调用 `server.Run()`\n456: - **THEN** HTTP 服务器启动\n457: - **AND** 在配置的端口监听\n458: - **AND** 记录启动消息\n459: \n460: #### Scenario: 启动失败\n461: - **GIVEN** 端口已被占用\n462: - **WHEN** 调用 `server.Run()`\n463: - **THEN** 返回错误\n464: - **AND** 服务器未启动\n465: \n466: #### Scenario: 优雅关闭\n467: - **GIVEN** 服务器正在运行\n468: - **WHEN** 接收终止信号\n469: - **THEN** 服务器优雅关闭\n470: - **AND** 活动请求完成\n471: \n472: ### Requirement: 工作区解析\n473: \n474: 系统 SHALL 正确解析和验证工作区目录。\n475: \n476: #### Scenario: 工作区从标志设置\n477: - **GIVEN** `-workspace /data/workspace` 标志\n478: - **WHEN** 服务器初始化\n479: - **THEN** 工作区解析为绝对路径 `/data/workspace`\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: 工作区默认为 CWD\n482: - **GIVEN** 无 `-workspace` 标志\n483: - **WHEN** 服务器初始化\n484: - **THEN** 工作区设置为当前工作目录\n485: - **AND** 如果 `os.Getwd()` 失败则致命错误\n486: \n487: #### Scenario: 工作区符号链接解析\n488: - **GIVEN** 工作区路径是符号链接\n489: - **WHEN** 服务器初始化\n490: - **THEN** 符号链接被解析\n491: - **AND** 使用解析后的绝对路径\n492: \n493: ### Requirement: 请求体大小限制\n494: \n495: 系统 SHALL 在 JWT 验证后限制请求体大小。\n496: \n497: #### Scenario: 应用大小限制\n498: - **GIVEN** JWT 验证成功\n499: - **WHEN** 请求通过中间件\n500: - **THEN** 请求体被包装在 `http.MaxBytesReader` 中\n501: - **AND** 限制为 32 MiB\n502: \n503: #### Scenario: 超过大小限制\n504: - **GIVEN** 请求体超过 32 MiB\n505: - **WHEN** 读取请求体\n506: - **THEN** 读取失败\n507: - **AND** 返回 HTTP 413（Payload Too Large）或等效错误\n508: \n509: ### Requirement: 时间记录\n510: \n511: 系统 SHALL 记录命令执行的开始和结束时间。\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: 记录开始时间\n514: - **GIVEN** 开始命令执行\n515: - **WHEN** 命令启动\n516: - **THEN** 记录 `start_time` 为当前时间\n517: \n518: #### Scenario: 记录结束时间\n519: - **GIVEN** 命令执行完成\n520: - **WHEN** 命令退出\n521: - **THEN** 记录 `end_time` 为当前时间\n522: - **AND** 计算并记录 `duration`\n523: \n524: ### Requirement: 上下文取消处理\n525: \n526: 系统 SHALL 正确处理命令执行的上下文取消。\n527: \n528: #### Scenario: 超时取消\n529: - **GIVEN** 命令执行超过配置的超时\n530: - **WHEN** 上下文截止时间超过\n531: - **THEN** 进程被终止\n532: - **AND** `exit_code` 设置为 124\n533: - **AND** stderr 包含超时消息\n534: \n535: #### Scenario: 手动取消\n536: - **GIVEN** 上下文被手动取消\n537: - **WHEN** 命令正在运行\n538: - **THEN** 进程被终止\n539: - **AND** 适当的错误处理\n540: \n541: ### Requirement: 环境变量合并\n542: \n543: 系统 SHALL 合并进程环境变量和请求环境变量。\n544: \n545: #### Scenario: 合并环境变量\n546: - **GIVEN** 进程有环境变量 `PATH=/usr/bin`\n547: - **AND** 请求有 `env: {\"NEW_VAR\": \"value\"}`\n548: - **WHEN** 命令执行\n549: - **THEN** `cmd.Env` 包含 `PATH=/usr/bin`\n550: - **AND** `cmd.Env` 包含 `NEW_VAR=value`\n551: \n552: #### Scenario: 环境变量覆盖\n553: - **GIVEN** 进程有环境变量 `PATH=/usr/bin`\n554: - **AND** 请求有 `env: {\"PATH\": \"/custom/path\"}`\n555: - **WHEN** 命令执行\n556: - **THEN** `cmd.Env` 中的 `PATH` 为 `/custom/path`\n557: - **AND** 请求环境变量优先\n558: \n559: ### Requirement: MIME 类型检测\n560: \n561: 系统 SHALL 基于文件扩展名检测 MIME 类型。\n562: \n563: #### Scenario: 已知扩展名\n564: - **GIVEN** 文件路径 `script.py`\n565: - **WHEN** 下载文件\n566: - **THEN** `Content-Type` 设置为 `text/x-python` 或 Python 的适当 MIME 类型\n567: \n568: #### Scenario: 未知扩展名\n569: - **GIVEN** 文件路径 `unknown.xyz`\n570: - **WHEN** 下载文件\n571: - **THEN** `Content-Type` 设置为 `application/octet-stream`\n572: \n573: ### Requirement: 目录创建模式\n574: \n575: 系统 SHALL 使用适当的权限创建目录。\n576: \n577: #### Scenario: 创建父目录\n578: - **GIVEN** 上传到路径 `sub1/sub2/file.txt`\n579: - **WHEN** 父目录不存在\n580: - **THEN** 创建 `sub1`，权限为 `0755`\n581: - **AND** 创建 `sub2`，权限为 `0755`\n582: \n583: ### Requirement: 日志记录\n584: \n585: 系统 SHALL 使用 klog 记录重要事件。\n586: \n587: #### Scenario: 启动日志\n588: - **GIVEN** 服务器启动\n589: - **WHEN** 初始化完成\n590: - **THEN** 记录配置信息（端口、工作区）\n591: \n592: #### Scenario: 请求日志\n593: - **GIVEN** Gin Logger 中间件已启用\n594: - **WHEN** 处理请求\n595: - **THEN** 记录请求方法、路径和状态码\n596: \n597: #### Scenario: 错误日志\n598: - **GIVEN** 发生错误\n599: - **WHEN** 错误被处理\n600: - **THEN** 记录错误详情\n601: - **AND** 不暴露敏感信息\n602: \n603: ### Requirement: 并发安全\n604: \n605: 系统 SHALL 安全处理并发请求。\n606: \n607: #### Scenario: 并发命令执行\n608: - **GIVEN** 多个并发执行请求\n609: - **WHEN** 请求被处理\n610: - **THEN** 每个命令隔离执行\n611: - **AND** 无竞态条件\n612: \n613: #### Scenario: 并发文件操作\n614: - **GIVEN** 多个并发文件上传\n615: - **WHEN** 文件被写入\n616: - **THEN** 每个文件独立处理\n617: - **AND** 文件系统操作正确\n618: \n619: ### Requirement: 零停止时间部署\n620: \n621: 系统 SHALL 支持零停止时间部署模式。\n622: \n623: #### Scenario: 优雅关闭\n624: - **GIVEN** 服务器接收 SIGTERM\n625: - **WHEN** 关闭信号被处理\n626: - **THEN** 停止接受新连接\n627: - **AND** 等待活动连接完成\n628: - **AND** 优雅关闭\n629: \n630: ### Requirement: 健康检查无认证\n631: \n632: 系统 SHALL 不需要对健康检查端点进行认证。\n633: \n634: #### Scenario: 健康检查在认证中间件外\n635: - **GIVEN** 路由已注册\n636: - **WHEN** 检查 `/health` 路由\n637: - **THEN** 不使用 `AuthMiddleware`\n638: - **AND** 可在无认证下访问\n639: \n640: #### Scenario: 健康检查返回服务信息\n641: - **GIVEN** 服务器正在运行\n642: - **WHEN** 调用 `GET /health`\n643: - **THEN** 响应包含服务名称\n644: - **AND** 响应包含版本\n645: - **AND** 响应包含正常运行时间\n646: \n647: ### Requirement: 工作区隔离\n648: \n649: 系统 SHALL 确保所有文件操作在工作区边界内。\n650: \n651: #### Scenario: 文件上传在工作区内\n652: - **GIVEN** 工作区为 `/workspace`\n653: - **AND** 上传到路径 `data/file.txt`\n654: - **WHEN** 文件被写入\n655: - **THEN** 文件在 `/workspace/data/file.txt`\n656: \n657: #### Scenario: 文件下载在工作区内\n658: - **GIVEN** 工作区为 `/workspace`\n659: - **AND** 请求下载 `data/file.txt`\n660: - **WHEN** 文件被读取\n661: - **THEN** 从 `/workspace/data/file.txt` 读取\n662: \n663: #### Scenario: 命令执行在工作区内\n664: - **GIVEN** 工作区为 `/workspace`\n665: - **AND** 工作目录为 `subdir`\n666: - **WHEN** 命令执行\n667: - **THEN** 命令在 `/workspace/subdir` 中执行\n668: \n669: ### Requirement: 错误代码映射\n670: \n671: 系统 SHALL 将错误映射到适当的 HTTP 状态代码。\n672: \n673: #### Scenario: 验证错误映射到 400\n674: - **GIVEN** 请求验证失败\n675: - **WHEN** 返回错误响应\n676: - **THEN** HTTP 状态码为 400\n677: \n678: #### Scenario: 认证错误映射到 401\n679: - **GIVEN** JWT 验证失败\n680: - **WHEN** 返回错误响应\n681: - **THEN** HTTP 状态码为 401\n682: \n683: #### Scenario: 未找到错误映射到 404\n684: - **GIVEN** 请求的文件或目录未找到\n685: - **WHEN** 返回错误响应\n686: - **THEN** HTTP 状态码为 404\n687: \n688: #### Scenario: 服务器错误映射到 500\n689: - **GIVEN** 发生内部服务器错误\n690: - **WHEN** 返回错误响应\n691: - **THEN** HTTP 状态码为 500\n\n(End of file - total 691 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 Delta Specification: PicoD 命令执行 API\n\n## Purpose\n\n实现 PicoD HTTP 守护进程的命令执行 API，为 AgentCube 平台的代码解释器沙箱提供安全的代码执行和文件管理能力。PicoD 在可配置的工作区 jail 中运行命令，管理工作区文件，并暴露健康检查端点和 JWT（RSA）保护的 API。\n\n## Base Specs\n\n- code-execution/spec.md: PicoD 命令执行 API 规范，包含所有 API 端点和行为的详细定义\n- code-execution/design.md: PicoD 设计文档，从源码推导的数据结构、常量和实现细节\n- deployment/client-go.md: Kubernetes 客户端库，用于 runtime API 类型（AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter CRDs）\n- proposal.md: AR-015 提案文档，概述 PicoD 的目的、范围、设计和实现策略\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: HTTP 服务器初始化\n\n系统 SHALL 初始化 Gin HTTP 服务器，使用可配置的监听端口和工作区根目录。\n\n#### Scenario: 使用默认配置初始化服务器","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775897502499,"end":1775897502529}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897502534,"sessionID":"ses_28442d047ffenRZ1MpYw8Va1pB","part":{"id":"prt_d7bbd5d6c001SjpnxnQ8HEscmX","messageID":"msg_d7bbd404c001eb4AZmnyuGVIK5","sessionID":"ses_28442d047ffenRZ1MpYw8Va1pB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-2d3e1f00f35940d6a42af2c7429711ab","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-041/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-041/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-041 Delta Specification: E2E 集成测试\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Provide end-to-end integration tests for the agentcube project, covering the complete lifecycle of AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources through the client-go library, including CRUD operations, watch/informer/lister functionality, error handling, and fake client behavior.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### REQ-001: AgentRuntime Lifecycle Integration Tests\n9: \n10: **Description**: Verify that AgentRuntime resources can be created, retrieved, updated, status-updated, deleted, and listed through the Kubernetes API server using the client-go library.\n11: \n12: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n13: - AgentRuntime creation succeeds with valid spec\n14: - AgentRuntime can be retrieved by name and namespace\n15: - AgentRuntime spec updates are persisted\n16: - AgentRuntime status updates are persisted independently of spec\n17: - AgentRuntime deletion removes the resource\n18: - AgentRuntime list operations return correct resources\n19: - Watch operations receive events for AgentRuntime changes\n20: \n21: **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n22: \n23: ```\n24: Scenario: Create AgentRuntime with valid spec\n25:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset for agentcube runtime API\n26:     AND a valid AgentRuntime spec with required fields (agent type, image, resource limits)\n27:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is created in a test namespace\n28:   THEN the creation succeeds with no error\n29:     AND the returned AgentRuntime has a generated UID\n30:     AND the returned AgentRuntime has creation timestamp set\n31:     AND the AgentRuntime spec matches the input spec\n32:     AND the AgentRuntime status is initialized to empty\n33: \n34: Scenario: Retrieve AgentRuntime by name\n35:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource in a test namespace\n36:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is retrieved by its name\n37:   THEN the retrieval succeeds with no error\n38:     AND the returned AgentRuntime matches the stored resource\n39:     AND all fields including metadata, spec, and status are preserved\n40: \n41: Scenario: Update AgentRuntime spec\n42:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n43:     AND a modified AgentRuntime spec (e.g., updated image tag)\n44:   WHEN the AgentRuntime spec is updated\n45:   THEN the update succeeds with no error\n46:     AND the returned AgentRuntime has the updated spec\n47:     AND the AgentRuntime resourceVersion is incremented\n48:     AND the AgentRuntime status is preserved unchanged\n49: \n50: Scenario: Update AgentRuntime status independently\n51:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n52:     AND an updated status (e.g., phase = Running, agentID set)\n53:   WHEN the AgentRuntime status is updated using UpdateStatus\n54:   THEN the update succeeds with no error\n55:     AND the returned AgentRuntime has the updated status\n56:     AND the AgentRuntime resourceVersion is incremented\n57:     AND the AgentRuntime spec is preserved unchanged\n58: \n59: Scenario: Delete AgentRuntime\n60:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n61:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is deleted by name\n62:   THEN the deletion succeeds with no error\n63:     AND subsequent retrieval of the AgentRuntime returns \"not found\" error\n64:     AND the AgentRuntime is removed from list results\n65: \n66: Scenario: List AgentRuntimes in namespace\n67:   GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources in a test namespace\n68:     AND AgentRuntime resources in other namespaces\n69:   WHEN AgentRuntimes are listed in the specific namespace\n70:   THEN the list succeeds with no error\n71:     AND the list contains only AgentRuntimes from that namespace\n72:     AND all AgentRuntimes in the namespace are present\n73:     AND AgentRuntimes from other namespaces are not present\n74: \n75: Scenario: List AgentRuntimes cluster-wide\n76:   GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources across different namespaces\n77:   WHEN AgentRuntimes are listed with no namespace filter\n78:   THEN the list succeeds with no error\n79:     AND the list contains AgentRuntimes from all namespaces\n80:     AND all AgentRuntimes in the cluster are present\n81: \n82: Scenario: Watch AgentRuntime for create events\n83:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n84:     AND an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes in a test namespace\n85:   WHEN a new AgentRuntime is created in the namespace\n86:   THEN the watch channel receives an ADDED event\n87:     AND the event contains the newly created AgentRuntime\n88:     AND the event type is correct (v1.Added)\n89: \n90: Scenario: Watch AgentRuntime for update events\n91:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n92:     AND an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes in its namespace\n93:   WHEN the AgentRuntime spec is updated\n94:   THEN the watch channel receives a MODIFIED event\n95:     AND the event contains the updated AgentRuntime\n96:     AND the event type is correct (v1.Modified)\n97: \n98: Scenario: Watch AgentRuntime for delete events\n99:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n100:     AND an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes in its namespace\n101:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is deleted\n102:   THEN the watch channel receives a DELETED event\n103:     AND the event contains the AgentRuntime before deletion\n104:     AND the event type is correct (v1.Deleted)\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### REQ-002: CodeInterpreter Lifecycle Integration Tests\n110: \n111: **Description**: Verify that CodeInterpreter resources can be created, retrieved, updated, status-updated, deleted, and listed through the Kubernetes API server using the client-go library.\n112: \n113: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n114: - CodeInterpreter creation succeeds with valid spec\n115: - CodeInterpreter can be retrieved by name and namespace\n116: - CodeInterpreter spec updates are persisted\n117: - CodeInterpreter status updates are persisted independently of spec\n118: - CodeInterpreter deletion removes the resource\n119: - CodeInterpreter list operations return correct resources\n120: - Watch operations receive events for CodeInterpreter changes\n121: \n122: **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n123: \n124: ```\n125: Scenario: Create CodeInterpreter with valid spec\n126:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset for agentcube runtime API\n127:     AND a valid CodeInterpreter spec with required fields (code, runtime, language)\n128:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter is created in a test namespace\n129:   THEN the creation succeeds with no error\n130:     AND the returned CodeInterpreter has a generated UID\n131:     AND the returned CodeInterpreter has creation timestamp set\n132:     AND the CodeInterpreter spec matches the input spec\n133:     AND the CodeInterpreter status is initialized to empty\n134: \n135: Scenario: Retrieve CodeInterpreter by name\n136:   GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource in a test namespace\n137:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter is retrieved by its name\n138:   THEN the retrieval succeeds with no error\n139:     AND the returned CodeInterpreter matches the stored resource\n140:     AND all fields including metadata, spec, and status are preserved\n141: \n142: Scenario: Update CodeInterpreter spec\n143:   GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource\n144:     AND a modified CodeInterpreter spec (e.g., updated code content)\n145:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter spec is updated\n146:   THEN the update succeeds with no error\n147:     AND the returned CodeInterpreter has the updated spec\n148:     AND the CodeInterpreter resourceVersion is incremented\n149:     AND the CodeInterpreter status is preserved unchanged\n150: \n151: Scenario: Update CodeInterpreter status independently\n152:   GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource\n153:     AND an updated status (e.g., executionResult, output)\n154:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter status is updated using UpdateStatus\n155:   THEN the update succeeds with no error\n156:     AND the returned CodeInterpreter has the updated status\n157:     AND the CodeInterpreter resourceVersion is incremented\n158:     AND the CodeInterpreter spec is preserved unchanged\n159: \n160: Scenario: Delete CodeInterpreter\n161:   GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource\n162:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter is deleted by name\n163:   THEN the deletion succeeds with no error\n164:     AND subsequent retrieval of the CodeInterpreter returns \"not found\" error\n165:     AND the CodeInterpreter is removed from list results\n166: \n167: Scenario: List CodeInterpreters in namespace\n168:   GIVEN multiple CodeInterpreter resources in a test namespace\n169:     AND CodeInterpreter resources in other namespaces\n170:   WHEN CodeInterpreters are listed in the specific namespace\n171:   THEN the list succeeds with no error\n172:     AND the list contains only CodeInterpreters from that namespace\n173:     AND all CodeInterpreters in the namespace are present\n174:     AND CodeInterpreters from other namespaces are not present\n175: \n176: Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter for create events\n177:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n178:     AND an active watch channel for CodeInterpreters in a test namespace\n179:   WHEN a new CodeInterpreter is created in the namespace\n180:   THEN the watch channel receives an ADDED event\n181:     AND the event contains the newly created CodeInterpreter\n182:     AND the event type is correct (v1.Added)\n183: \n184: Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter for delete events\n185:   GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource\n186:     AND an active watch channel for CodeInterpreters in its namespace\n187:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter is deleted\n188:   THEN the watch channel receives a DELETED event\n189:     AND the event contains the CodeInterpreter before deletion\n190:     AND the event type is correct (v1.Deleted)\n191: ```\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ### REQ-003: Informer and Lister Integration Tests\n196: \n197: **Description**: Verify that SharedInformerFactory and listers work correctly for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, including cache synchronization and event handling.\n198: \n199: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n200: - Informers successfully start and sync cache\n201: - Listers return cached resources\n202: - Informer event handlers receive resource changes\n203: - Multiple informers can share the same factory\n204: - Cache resync works correctly\n205: \n206: **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n207: \n208: ```\n209: Scenario: AgentRuntime informer syncs existing resources\n210:   GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources in a test namespace\n211:     AND a SharedInformerFactory configured for the namespace\n212:     AND an AgentRuntime informer from the factory\n213:   WHEN the informer is started\n214:     AND WaitForCacheSync is called\n215:   THEN the cache sync completes successfully\n216:     AND the AgentRuntime lister returns all existing AgentRuntimes\n217:     AND all resources are cached with correct metadata\n218: \n219: Scenario: AgentRuntime informer receives create events\n220:   GIVEN a started AgentRuntime informer\n221:     AND a registered event handler for AgentRuntimes\n222:   WHEN a new AgentRuntime is created\n223:   THEN the event handler receives an OnAdd event\n224:     AND the event handler is called with the new AgentRuntime\n225:     AND the AgentRuntime is immediately available in the lister cache\n226: \n227: Scenario: AgentRuntime informer receives update events\n228:   GIVEN a started AgentRuntime informer with existing resources\n229:     AND a registered event handler for AgentRuntimes\n230:   WHEN an existing AgentRuntime is updated\n231:   THEN the event handler receives an OnUpdate event\n232:     AND the event handler is called with old and new objects\n233:     AND the updated AgentRuntime is immediately reflected in the lister cache\n234: \n235: Scenario: AgentRuntime informer receives delete events\n236:   GIVEN a started AgentRuntime informer with existing resources\n237:     AND a registered event handler for AgentRuntimes\n238:   WHEN an existing AgentRuntime is deleted\n239:   THEN the event handler receives an OnDelete event\n240:     AND the event handler is called with the deleted AgentRuntime\n241:     AND the AgentRuntime is removed from the lister cache\n242: \n243: Scenario: Multiple informers share same factory\n244:   GIVEN a SharedInformerFactory configured for a test namespace\n245:     AND an AgentRuntime informer from the factory\n246:     AND a CodeInterpreter informer from the same factory\n247:   WHEN both informers are started\n248:     AND WaitForCacheSync is called for both types\n249:   THEN both informers sync successfully\n250:     AND both listers return correct resources\n251:     AND the factory manages a single cache for both resource types\n252: \n253: Scenario: AgentRuntime lister with label selector\n254:   GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources with different labels in a test namespace\n255:     AND a synced AgentRuntime lister\n256:   WHEN AgentRuntimes are listed with a label selector\n257:   THEN the list returns only AgentRuntimes matching the labels\n258:     AND non-matching AgentRuntimes are excluded\n259: \n260: Scenario: CodeInterpreter namespace lister Get by name\n261:   GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource in a test namespace\n262:     AND a synced CodeInterpreter namespace lister\n263:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter is retrieved by name using the namespace lister\n264:   THEN the retrieval succeeds with no error\n265:     AND the returned CodeInterpreter matches the stored resource\n266: ```\n267: \n268: ---\n269: \n270: ### REQ-004: Error Handling and Edge Cases\n271: \n272: **Description**: Verify that the client-go library handles errors, edge cases, and invalid inputs correctly.\n273: \n274: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n275: - Invalid spec returns appropriate error\n276: - Resource conflicts are detected\n277: - Watch handles disconnection and reconnection\n278: - Concurrent modifications are detected\n279: \n280: **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n281: \n282: ```\n283: Scenario: Create AgentRuntime with invalid spec\n284:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n285:     AND an invalid AgentRuntime spec (missing required fields)\n286:   WHEN the AgentRuntime creation is attempted\n287:   THEN the creation fails with a validation error\n288:     AND the error message indicates the validation failure\n289:     AND no AgentRuntime resource is created\n290: \n291: Scenario: Update AgentRuntime with stale resourceVersion\n292:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n293:     AND an AgentRuntime object with an outdated resourceVersion\n294:   WHEN the AgentRuntime update is attempted\n295:   THEN the update fails with a conflict error\n296:     AND the error indicates resource version conflict\n297:     AND the AgentRuntime remains unchanged\n298: \n299: Scenario: Delete non-existent AgentRuntime\n300:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n301:     AND a non-existent AgentRuntime name in a test namespace\n302:   WHEN the AgentRuntime deletion is attempted\n303:   THEN the deletion fails with a \"not found\" error\n304: \n305: Scenario: Get non-existent CodeInterpreter\n306:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n307:     AND a non-existent CodeInterpreter name in a test namespace\n308:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter retrieval is attempted\n309:   THEN the retrieval fails with a \"not found\" error\n310: \n311: Scenario: Watch handles server disconnection\n312:   GIVEN an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes\n313:   WHEN the API server connection is temporarily lost\n314:     AND then re-established\n315:   THEN the watch channel reconnects automatically\n316:     AND events continue to be received after reconnection\n317:     AND no duplicate events are received for the same change\n318: \n319: Scenario: List with field selector\n320:   GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources in different states\n321:     AND a configured Kubernetes clientset\n322:   WHEN AgentRuntimes are listed with a field selector (e.g., status.phase=Running)\n323:   THEN the list succeeds with no error\n324:     AND the list contains only AgentRuntimes matching the field selector\n325: ```\n326: \n327: ---\n328: \n329: ### REQ-005: Fake Client Integration Tests\n330: \n331: **Description**: Verify that fake clients work correctly for testing purposes, including CRUD operations and watch behavior.\n332: \n333: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n334: - Fake clientset supports all CRUD operations\n335: - Fake clients track resources in memory\n336: - Watch operations work with fake clients\n337: - Fake clients can be used in unit tests\n338: \n339: **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n340: \n341: ```\n342: Scenario: Fake clientset creates AgentRuntime\n343:   GIVEN a fake clientset initialized with Scheme registration\n344:     AND a valid AgentRuntime spec\n345:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is created using the fake client\n346:   THEN the creation succeeds with no error\n347:     AND the AgentRuntime is stored in the fake client's memory\n348:     AND the AgentRuntime can be retrieved by name\n349: \n350: Scenario: Fake clientset updates AgentRuntime\n351:   GIVEN a fake clientset with an existing AgentRuntime\n352:     AND a modified AgentRuntime spec\n353:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is updated using the fake client\n354:   THEN the update succeeds with no error\n355:     AND the AgentRuntime in memory reflects the update\n356:     AND subsequent retrieval returns the updated AgentRuntime\n357: \n358: Scenario: Fake clientset deletes AgentRuntime\n359:   GIVEN a fake clientset with an existing AgentRuntime\n360:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is deleted using the fake client\n361:   THEN the deletion succeeds with no error\n362:     AND the AgentRuntime is removed from memory\n363:     AND subsequent retrieval returns \"not found\" error\n364: \n365: Scenario: Fake clientset watch for AgentRuntimes\n366:   GIVEN a fake clientset\n367:     AND an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes\n368:   WHEN an AgentRuntime is created\n369:   THEN the watch channel receives an ADDED event\n370:     AND the event contains the newly created AgentRuntime\n371: ```\n372: \n373: ---\n374: \n375: ## Test Infrastructure\n376: \n377: ### Test Setup\n378: - Use `test/e2e` package\n379: - Require a running Kubernetes API server (can use envtest for local testing)\n380: - Create temporary test namespaces for isolation\n381: - Clean up test resources after each test\n382: \n383: ### Dependencies\n384: - `k8s.io/client-go` for Kubernetes client\n385: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` for generated clients\n386: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/envtest` for local test environment\n387: \n388: ### Test Naming Convention\n389: - Test functions: `Test<ModuleName>_<ScenarioName>`\n390: - Subtests: `/<GIVEN/WHEN/THEN_Concise_Description>`\n391: \n392: ### Assertions\n393: - Use `assert` package from `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert`\n394: - Verify no errors returned\n395: - Verify returned objects match expected values\n396: - Verify resourceVersion changes on updates\n397: - Verify UID and timestamps on creation\n\n(End of file - total 397 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-041 Delta Specification: E2E 集成测试\n\n## Purpose\nProvide end-to-end integration tests for the agentcube project, covering the complete lifecycle of AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources through the client-go library, including CRUD operations, watch/informer/lister functionality, error handling, and fake client behavior.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: AgentRuntime Lifecycle Integration Tests\n\n**Description**: Verify that AgentRuntime resources can be created, retrieved, updated, status-updated, deleted, and listed through the Kubernetes API server using the client-go library.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- AgentRuntime creation succeeds with valid spec\n- AgentRuntime can be retrieved by name and namespace\n- AgentRuntime spec updates are persisted\n- AgentRuntime status updates are persisted independently of spec\n- AgentRuntime deletion removes the resource\n- AgentRuntime list operations return correct resources\n- Watch operations receive events for AgentRuntime changes\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-041/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775897502494,"end":1775897502532}}}}
